HEADWORD: Burrock
<hw>Bur"rock</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Perh. from AS.
<ets>burg</ets>, <ets>burh</ets>, hill + <ets>-ock</ets>.]</ety> <def>A
small weir or dam in a river to direct the stream to gaps where fish
traps are placed.</def> <rj><au>Knight.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
